Chairman of the Senate Committee on Agriculture, Senator Abdullahi Adamu (APC, Nasarawa) yesterday opened an intensive training program for youth on poultry farming. Hundreds of youth and women from Nasarawa West senatorial district are being trained at the New Keffi Hotel in Keffi, Nasarawa State on poultry production. The senator said the training was conceived to reduce unemployment, boost food security and economy of the country. He said the training would provide participants with necessary skills for modern techniques in poultry production. In his remark, the acting executive secretary of the Lake Chad Research Institute, Dr Kallison Gwadi said the training would take participants out of the labour market.